metadata:
  section_id: 40
  hadith_first: 7570
  hadith_last: 7600

hadiths[31]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}: 7570,"The Prophet ﷺ  said, ""Do you want to kill it with a harsh death? Did you sharpen your knife before putting it to her neck?""",,, 7571,"""He (saw) said: Allah, the Blessed and Exalted, said, 'Mention the name of Allah over them as they are lined up.' He (saw) said, 'Stand in three straight lines which are reasonable, in the name of Allah, and Allah is Greater. O Allah, it is from You and to You.'""",,, 7572,"""Don't eat.""",,, 7573,"The polytheists disputed with them, so they said, ""They did not kill, they only ate, and Allah did not kill, they did not eat.""",,, 7574,"There is no person who kills a small bird or anything larger for no just reason, but Allah, the Mighty and Sublime, will ask him about it. It was said: ""O Messenger of Allah, what does just reason;' mean?"" Her said: ""That you slaughter it and eat it, and do not cut off its head and throw it aside."" (Using translation from Nasāʾī 4349)",,, 7575,"""The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  cursed whoever imitates or represents with animals.""",,, 7576,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  said to Abu Al-Haytham ibn Al-Tayhan, ""Beware of onions and garlic, slaughter a sheep for us."" So Abu Al-Haytham commanded his wife to knead dough for them, and he cut the meat and cooked and grilled it.",,, 7577,"Regarding the Prophet ﷺ , it is mentioned that he prohibited the slaughter of pregnant animals and trading with goods before the rising of the sun. Al-Dhahabi remained silent about this in his summary.",,, 7578,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, ""There are forty qualities that Allah has bestowed upon His servant, and whoever possesses any of them without seeking its reward or believing in its promise, Allah will enter him into paradise through it.""",,, 7579,"The Prophet ﷺ  and his companions passed by a woman who slaughtered a sheep for them and prepared food for them. When they returned, she said, ""O Messenger of Allah, we have prepared food for you, so come and eat."" The Prophet ﷺ  and his companions entered and they would not start eating until the Prophet ﷺ  began. He took a bite but could not swallow it, so the Prophet ﷺ  said, ""This sheep was slaughtered without the permission of its owner."" The woman said, ""O Prophet of Allah, we do not feel shy about the family of Mu'adh, and they do not feel shy about us. We take from them and they take from us.""",,, 7580,"""From Jabir ibn Abdullah, he said: 'They slaughtered on the day of Khaybar the red camels, the mules, and the horses. Then the Prophet ﷺ forbade them from slaughtering the red camels and mules, but he did not forbid them from slaughtering the horses.'""",,, 7581,"he caught two rabbits and he could not find a knife with which to slaughter then, so he slaughtered them with Marwah. Then he came to the Prophet and said: ""O Mesenger of Allah! I caught two rabbits but I could not find a knife with which to slaughter them, so I slaughtered them with Marwah;l can I eat them?"" He said: ""Eat (them)."" (Using translation from Nasāʾī 4399)",,, 7582,"From Nubayshah, he said: A man asked the Prophet ﷺ saying, ""O Messenger of Allah, we used to offer sacrifices during the pre-Islamic period of Ignorance in the month of Rajab. What do you command us to do?"" The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, ""Offer sacrifices to Allah in any month you want and do good deeds for Allah, and feed the needy.""",,, 7583,"""The Prophet ﷺ  ordered for division of inheritance every five to one.""",,, 7584,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  was asked about ""al-fara'"", and he said, ""Al-fara' is a right, and even if you leave it until it becomes the offspring of a she-camel or a ewe, it is still incumbent upon you to take care of it for the sake of Allah, or to give it to a widow. This is better than slaughtering it, as its meat will stick to its bones, and you will drive it with your camel."" (Narration reported in Sahih Muslim)",,, 7585,"""In the Far'ah, it is a right (i.e., a means of settling a debt) that cannot be delayed or postponed. It is the first and the most important among all the debts that one owes. It sticks to your hand, but you can pay it off with milk until it becomes a matter of financial choice, then you can slaughter it.""",,, 7586,"""I saw the Messenger of Allah (pbuh) and said to him, 'Seek forgiveness for me.' He replied, 'May Allah forgive you.' I said to him, 'Is this once or twice?' A man asked him, 'O Messenger of Allah, what do you think about debts and loans?' The Messenger of Allah (pbuh) replied, 'Whoever wishes to keep his debts can keep them, and whoever wishes to cancel them can cancel them. As for the sheep, it is the sacrifice for it.'""",,, 7587,"Every boy is in pledge for his 'Aqiqah, so slaughter (the animal) for him on the seventh day, and shave his head, and a name (Using translation from Nasāʾī 4220)",,, 7588,The Prophet ﷺ performed 'Aqiqah for Hasan and Husain on the seventh day and named them. He also instructed that their heads be shaved.,,, 7589,"That Ali bin Abi Talib said: ""The Messenger of Allah ﷺ had the 'Aqiqah for Al-Hasan with one sheep, and said: 'O Fatimah! Shave his head and give the weight of his hair in silver as charity.'"" He said: ""So I weighed it, and it was the weight of a Dirham or a bit of a Dirham."" (Using translation from Tirmidhī 1519)",,, 7590,"That the Prophet ﷺ  performed Aqiqah for each of Al-Hasan and Al-Husayn with two similar, equal-sized, and defect-free lambs. This hadith is narrated by Suwar ibn Abi Hamza and is considered weak.",,, 7591,"I heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  saying, ""Take care of birds and their nests."" Sahih",,, 7592,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  was asked about Aqeeqah, so he said, ""I do not like disobedience. Whoever from amongst you has a child born to him, let him offer a sacrifice on his behalf. For a boy, two sheep are to be sacrificed, and for a girl, one sheep is to be sacrificed.""",,, 7593,"I heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  say, ""With a newborn boy, there is a sacrificial offering, so spill blood for him and remove harm from him."" Jarir asked Al-Hasan about the harm, and he said, ""It refers to the hair.""",,, 7594,"""We were in the Jahiliyyah (pre-Islamic era) when a boy was born to us, we would slaughter a sheep for him, shave his head, and rub his head with its blood. But when Islam came, we would slaughter a sheep for him, shave his head, and rub his head with saffron.""",,, 7595,"And about the female sheep, it is slaughtered regularly and its bone is not broken, so it can be eaten, fed, and donated. Let this happen on the seventh day, and if not, then on the fourteenth day. And if not, then on the twenty-first day.",,, 7596,"""I was blessed with a son, and I was with the Prophet ﷺ. I said, 'I wish to give you his place as a loaf of bread and meat.' The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, 'If you say that, surely they will be stingy and disappointed, but they are the fruits of hearts and the delight of the eyes.'""",,, 7597,The Prophet ﷺ said: Whatever is cut off of an animal when it is alive is dead. (Using translation from Abū Dāʾūd 2858),,, 7598,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  was asked about the cutting of the ear of camels and the marking of sheep, and he said, ""Whatever is cut from a living animal is considered dead.""",,, 7599,"We were with the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  on a journey, and we passed by a tree with two red chicks. We took them, then the mother came to the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  while chirping. The Prophet ﷺ  said, ""Who has taken her chicks?"" We said, ""We did."" He said, ""Return them.""",,, 7600,"“I said: ‘O Messenger of Allah, we hunt game but we cannot find anything but the sharp edge of a stone or stick (with which to slaughter it).’ He said: ‘Cause the blood to flow with whatever you want, and mention the Name of Allah over it.’” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3177)",,,
